    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-08-27T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-08-27T06:00:00-05:00" n="254"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d254">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A16/51: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The American Representative on the Special Commission</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-08-27T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 27, 1928—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received August 27—9:12 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. Article V of your draft of treaty discussing category III appears to limit
                    “civil aircraft” to those “manufactured under military specifications.”
                    Examination of Traffic in Arms Convention discloses no such limitation and I
                    would appreciate analysis of Department’s views in this matter. I have requested
                        Yount<note n="59" xml:id="d254fn59">Major Burton K. Yount, assistant
                        military attaché for air, American Embassy, Paris.</note> to proceed from
                    Paris to advise me on this and other questions.</p>
                <p>I assume that full publicity concerning aircraft is made by our Government
                    departments. If this is so could we not safely promise full publicity on “civil
                    aviation” without limitation?</p>
                <p>Address Ammission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
